      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 55: Catching startForeground() and continuing leaves a service that was started via startForegroundService() without promotion; Android can still kill the process shortly afterwards. If promotion fails, stop the service immediately after logging so it does not remain in an invalid lifecycle state.\n```suggestion\n} catch (e: Exception) {\n    android.util.Log.w(\"PushForegroundService\", \"startForeground failed\", e)\n    stopSelf(startId)\n    return START_NOT_STICKY\n}\n```",
